title: Sussan Ley’s allies urge Angus Taylor’s backers ‘put your name to it’ amid leadership plot to oust her
summary_full: Push discussed in private talks and echoes tactic of then-Liberal prime minister Malcolm Turnbull used against Peter DuttonFollow our Australia news live blog for latest updatesGet our breaking news email, free app or daily news podcastSussan Ley’s allies want the Liberal leader to demand her rivals put their names to a petition calling for a spill, forcing Angus Taylor’s backers to publicly reveal themselves as plotting to oust her.The push was discussed in private talks on Tuesday and has echoes of the tactic then-Liberal prime minister Malcolm Turnbull used to stall Peter Dutton’s ultimately failed leadership coup in 2018.
